Description: Persistent SSH terminal sessions with tmux integration
 ShellKeep is a cross-platform SSH terminal manager backed by tmux.
 It automatically saves and restores your session layout per device,
 supports multiple environments (named groups of sessions), and
 reconnects seamlessly after network interruptions.
 .
 Features include per-device layout persistence, named environments,
 automatic reconnection with exponential backoff, session history,
 and tray icon integration.
 .
 ShellKeep is NOT registered as x-terminal-emulator because it is not
 a local terminal — it is an SSH session manager.
